  "25": {
    "John T. Carroll": "b. Literally, \u201cwhether the ones who are being saved [are] few.\u201d\nc. Most textual witnesses, including \u05d0 A, conform this phrase to the parallel in\nv. 25:\n\u201cI do not know you [or] where you are from\u201d (i.e., by adding the accusative pronoun\nhymas). I take that to be a scribal improvement and prefer the shorter text (with \u220f75 B\nL 070 1241 2542).\nd. Or \u201call of you who do what is wrong [unjust]\u201d (i.e., an objective genitive).\n[22\u201330]\nv. 25,\nqueries the authoritative teacher about the scope of salvation: \u201cAre only a few\nbeing saved?\u201d (\nv. 25). There\nis no mistaking the narrative representations of this parabolic kyrios and his\nrefused guests, given their presumption and the protest it (mis)informs: \u201cWe\nate in your presence and drank,\u201d and \u201cyou taught in our streets\u201d (",
    "John Trapp": "But first must he suffer ] He must, because God would have it so. Voluntas Dei, necessitas rei.\n25. But first must he suffer] He must, because God would have it so. Voluntas Dei, necessitas rei."
  },
